sec.p:
The quantitative data were analysed using Stata version 13.1. At baseline, 3-, 6-, 9-, and 12-month follow-up, the number of individuals who were taking different types of antidepressants (or combination therapy) were tabulated. Comparisons between data collected at: baseline and 3 months; 3 and 6 months; 6 and 9 months; and 9 and 12 months were undertaken in order to determine the number of participants who:
had continued on the same medication;
had an increased dose of medication;
had switched antidepressant medication;
received a second antidepressant (combination therapy) or whose treatment was augmented with another drug; or
stopped (or re-started) antidepressants.
